/*
Complexity note:
- Time: O(n * R) where R is the number of distinct reachable sums encountered (bounded by the range of possible sums). Using a Set keeps the implementation simple and correct for negative values. For typical weight arrays used by the service (several hundred items with modest magnitudes) this is practical. If you encounter very large magnitudes or need stricter performance guarantees, consider a bitset-based DP with an offseted range or other optimizations.
- Space: O(R) for the reachable sums set.
*/

