Add the helper to your DB connection utilities and a small test script. Below is a minimal, self-contained implementation and corresponding tests that meet the requirements.

File: lib/DB/Connection/Util.pm

package DB::Connection::Util;

use strict;
use warnings;
use Exporter 'import';

our @EXPORT_OK = qw(construct_mongodb_uri);

# construct_mongodb_uri($base_uri, $username, $password)
# - Returns an empty string if any argument is undefined or an empty string.
# - If $base_uri starts with "mongodb://" or "mongodb+srv://" injects
#   "username:password@" immediately after the protocol.
# - If the prefix is not one of the two supported mongodb prefixes,
#   returns the original $base_uri unchanged.
# - Leaves username/password characters as-is (per examples).
sub construct_mongodb_uri {
    my ($base_uri, $username, $password) = @_;

    # Return empty string if any argument is undefined or empty string
    return "" unless defined $base_uri && defined $username && defined $password;
    return "" if $base_uri eq '' || $username eq '' || $password eq '';

    # Inject credentials for supported MongoDB URI prefixes
    if ($base_uri =~ m{^mongodb\+srv://}) {
        $base_uri =~ s{^mongodb\+srv://}{mongodb+srv://$username:$password@};
    }
    elsif ($base_uri =~ m{^mongodb://}) {
        $base_uri =~ s{^mongodb://}{mongodb://$username:$password@};
    }

    return $base_uri;
}

1;


File: t/construct_mongodb_uri.t

#!/usr/bin/env perl

use strict;
use warnings;
use Test::More tests => 5;

use FindBin;
use lib "$FindBin::Bin/../lib";
use DB::Connection::Util qw(construct_mongodb_uri);

# Examples and requirement checks
is(
    construct_mongodb_uri("mongodb://host:27017", "user", "pass"),
    "mongodb://user:pass@host:27017",
    'mongodb://host:27017 -> credentials injected with port'
);

is(
    construct_mongodb_uri("mongodb+srv://cluster.example.com", "user", "p@ss$!"),
    "mongodb+srv://user:p@ss$!@cluster.example.com",
    'mongodb+srv:// cluster -> credentials injected, special chars preserved'
);

is(
    construct_mongodb_uri("http://example", "user", "pass"),
    "http://example",
    'non-mongodb prefix -> original string returned'
);

is(
    construct_mongodb_uri("mongodb://host", "", "pass"),
    "",
    'empty username -> empty string returned'
);

is(
    construct_mongodb_uri("", "user", "pass"),
    "",
    'empty base_uri -> empty string returned'
);

# End of tests


Notes:
- The implementation intentionally does not percent-encode username/password characters because the supplied acceptance examples expect credentials to appear verbatim (e.g. p@ss$!). If you later decide to follow the MongoDB URI specification strictly, add URL-encoding for username and password before insertion.
- Place the module under lib/ and the test under t/ and run the tests with: perl t/construct_mongodb_uri.t or using prove.

